de.bkroeger.myvisio.svg.elements

Class SVGElementImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.tree.DefaultMutableTreeNode
      • de.bkroeger.myvisio.svg.elements.SVGElementImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.tree.MutableTreeNode, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode, SVGElement, SVGLangSpace, SVGStylable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SVGContainerElementImpl, SVGDescElementImpl, SVGGraphicalElementImpl, SVGTextElementImpl, SVGTitleElementImpl

    public class SVGElementImpl
extends javax.swing.tree.DefaultMutableTreeNode
implements SVGElement, SVGLangSpace, SVGStylable

    Dies ist die Implementierung des Interface SVGElement und damit die Basisklasse für alle SVG-Elemente.

    Zur Abbildung der SVG-Hierarchie erweitert die Klasse die Klasse DefaultMutableTreeNode. Damit können Parent-Child-Beziehungen in beiden Richtungen durchsucht werden.

    Author:
    bk

      • parseConditionalProcessingAttributes

        public void parseConditionalProcessingAttributes(org.w3c.dom.Element elem)
        A conditional processing attribute is one that controls whether or not the element on which it appears is processed. Most elements, but not all, may have conditional processing attributes specified on them. See Conditional processing for details. The conditional processing attributes defined in SVG 1.1 are ‘requiredExtensions’, ‘requiredFeatures’ and ‘systemLanguage’.

      • parseGraphicalEventAttributes

      • parsePresentationAttributes

        protected void parsePresentationAttributes(org.w3c.dom.Element elem)
                                    throws TechnicalException
        An XML attribute on an SVG element which specifies a value for a given property for that element. Note that although any property may be specified on any element, not all properties will apply to (affect the rendering of) a given element.
        Throws:
        TechnicalException

      • parseXml

        protected void parseXml(org.w3c.dom.Element elem)
                 throws TechnicalException

        Analysiert die Standard-Attribute des DOM-Elements.

        The core attributes are those attributes that can be specified on any SVG element. See Common attributes. The core attributes are ‘id’, ‘xml:base’, ‘xml:lang’ and ‘xml:space’.
